main event: Three irregularly shaped objects were observed moving slowly and changing direction over Grand Cayman Island, West Indies from October 22-25, 1961.
interesting points: The objects were described as irregularly shaped, moving slowly, and changing direction.
Some observers thought the objects were aircraft, but others disagreed.
The case was listed as having insufficient data to fully evaluate the sighting.
The observers likely lacked sufficient knowledge of higher atmospheric phenomena to properly assess the sighting.

The Air Force requested additional information about the sighting, including the comparative size of the objects, their elevation and azimuth when first and last observed, how long the witnesses observed them, and complete weather data.
